The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Friday, July 01, 2005 

 IIM for IAS

 Calcutta, June 30: The government will arrange training for senior administrative officials at Indian Institute of Management, Joka.

 We are having talks with the IIM authorities and the training programme for senior IAS officers will be organised soon, the chief minister said today. The training, he added while replying to discussions on the budget for the home (personnel and administrative reforms) department, was essential to improve their administrative skill and efficiency.




